task.summary: Updated Multi-Use Pattern to v1.2 - Removed all labels from the l_LgBeam (alignment marker) layer to prevent cases where pattern us updated in between exposure of the alignment marks and the structures, causing them to not match. - Also added possibility to include an apparent wafer radius to the _place_blocks() function. Allowing for blocks to be placed even if they hang off the wafer (by a small amount). - Modified the add_theory_cell(), add_chip_labels(), add_tem_membranes() and similar cells to now add their features directly to the blocks using a "for block in self.blocks:" statement. This allows then for the export of a single block with all of these features on it for aligned e-beam writing. Before the block export didn't have these features as they were written at the top level.
-Converted whole project to Python 3.6! -Simplified the file structure so that it now only uses a single gdsCAD project.
